The PA and office manager to Uasin Gishu Senator Isaac Melly were charged in Eldoret with two counts of attempted bank fraud. They denied the charges and were released on a cash bail of Sh300,000.Amos Sang (the office manager) and Stephen Biwott (the PA) were charged alongside a third suspect Morris Mwavizo alias Francis Nderitu Kamaru, before principal magistrate Charles Obulutsa.The first count against the trio states that on October 14, 2015, at Equity Bank market branch in Eldoret town, Uasin Gishu county, they jointly conspired to defraud the said bank of Sh500,000.A day later, on October 15, 2015, they attempted to defraud the same bank of Sh4 million. Customer service supervisor Naomi Kemundo told the court how the trio came to the bank enquiring how they could withdraw the money, which they claimed was meant for buying building materials for the senator&rsquo;s house. The trio, Kemundo said, had managed to withdraw Sh500,000 from an account belonging to one of the bank&rsquo;s clients without his consent.&ldquo;I showed them the procedure of withdrawing the huge sum,&rdquo; Kemundo said.It was after they came to the bank on the second day to withdraw Sh4 million that the bank detected the anomaly and raised the alarm, leading to the arrest of the senator&rsquo;s office manager and personal assistant.She said the first accused managed to escape and is still at large .She said when the police detectives came; they picked up five bank employees for interrogation and later released.